JOS – A Plateau governorship aspirant on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Nde Victor Dimka, has promised to bequeath a united, secure and prosperous Plateau if elected Governor in 2023. Dimka, a former Controller of Nigeria Customs Service (NCS), stated this on Friday in Kanke Local Government Area (LGA) his country home when he officially declared his intention to contest for the number one seat in Plateau state. “I am a Fellow of the Security Institute and I know that security is everything. “If you ask me to name three important things; I will tell you that one is security, two is security, three is security,” he stressed. The Customs Ex-Controller told his party stakeholders that “with my experience, I will bequeath I peaceful, united and prosperous Plateau.” The governorship hopeful added that he has the capacity and experience to make Plateau envy of other states. Kanke Local Government APC Chairman, Mr William Gombwer on his part, appreciated those vying for elective positions on the platform of APC. Gombwer noted that without the aspirant the party wouldn’t have been as strong as it is. POLL The Kanke LGA chairman urged the aspirants and their supporters to conduct themselves peacefully as they go about their campaigns. He called on APC members to team up with whoever emerged as the party’s candidate and ensure that the party wins the secondary election. Mr Menshak Chindaba, Director General, DVD Movement hinted that Kanke LGA had been looking for an opportunity to govern Plateau in the last 48 years. According to Chindaba, the stakeholders have searched and believe that Dimka is the most qualified to bring their dream to reality. The DG noted that after retirement, many political parties wooed Dimka to join them but he decided to pitch his tenth with APC on the Plateau.